-- Japanese Bought Net 243.7 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-05-23T23:51:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/japanese-bought-net-243-7-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended May 18 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 243.7 billion yen ($3.1 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 36.1 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 33.6 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 241.2 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 64.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 131.3 billion yen in stocks, and sold 896.1 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 1092.1
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
